gle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104paj1665702776864.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/paj1665702776864.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/paj1665702776864.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"paj1665702776864\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SQL Support on Informix\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript command and the SQL Editor are\n      supported.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"paj1665702776864__section_o3z_g1f_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d940670e54\">Monitoring SQL in the message frame</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"paj1665702776864__p_d50954e1_d50955e1_d50956e1\">This is supported, although you cannot see the actual\n            values used in the SQL statements.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"paj1665702776864__section_wj3_j1f_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d940670e63\">Special Considerations</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"paj1665702776864__p_d50960e1_d50961e1_d50962e1\">Consider the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"paj1665702776864__ul_dtw_j1f_jcc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paj1665702776864__li_d24374e1_d24375e1_d24376e1\">For the single connection mechanism, never use\n               the <code class=\"ph codeph\">commit work</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">rollback</code> instructions in an SQL\n               string with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> instruction, or in SQL Edit. However, if you\n               do not have an Informix front-end and you have not yet created an Informix database,\n               you cannot log on to Informix. In this case, use SQL Edit. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paj1665702776864__li_d24377e1_d24378e1_d24379e1\">You cannot select, insert or update BLOB fields\n               in SQL Edit or with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> instruction. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530837\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530837\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SQL Support on Informix Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SQL Support on Informix The sql ProcScript command and the SQL Editor are supported. Monitoring SQL in the message frame This is supported, although you cannot see the actual values used in the SQL statements. Special Considerations Consider the following: For the single connection mechanism, never use the commit work or rollback instructions in an SQL string with the sql instruction, or in SQL Edit. However, if you do not have an Informix front-end and you have not yet created an Informix database, you cannot log on to Informix. In this case, use SQL Edit. You cannot select, insert or update BLOB fields in SQL Edit or with the sql instruction. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}